Name: hypomyelinating leukodystrophy 2
Definition: A hypomyelinating leukodystrophy characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance of nystagmus

Name: hypomyelinating leukodystrophy 10
Definition: A hypomyelinating leukodystrophy characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance of progressive postnatal microcephaly

Name: hypomyelinating leukodystrophy 4
Definition: A hypomyelinating leukodystrophy characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance of hypotonia
Synonym: Pelizaeus-Merzbacher-like disease due to HSPD1 mutation

Name: hypomyelinating leukodystrophy 3
Definition: A hypomyelinating leukodystrophy characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance of early infantile onset of global developmental delay
Synonym: Pelizaeus-Merzbacher-like disease due to AIMP1 mutation

Name: hypomyelinating leukodystrophy 9
Definition: A hypomyelinating leukodystrophy characterized by delayed psychomotor development

Name: hypomyelinating leukodystrophy 11
Definition: A hypomyelinating leukodystrophy characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance of delayed psychomotor development and other neurologic features associated with hypomyelination that has_material_basis_in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the POLR1C gene on chromosome 6p21.

Name: hypomyelinating leukodystrophy 5
Definition: A hypomyelinating leukodystrophy characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance of congenital cataract

Name: hypomyelinating leukodystrophy 7 with or without oligodontia and-or hypogonadotropic hypogonadism
Definition: A hypomyelinating leukodystrophy characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance of hildhood onset of progressive motor decline manifest as spasticity

Name: hypomyelinating leukodystrophy 13
Definition: A hypomyelinating leukodystrophy characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance of infantile onset of delayed psychomotor development

Name: hypomyelinating leukodystrophy 12
Definition: A hypomyelinating leukodystrophy characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance of severely delayed or even lack of psychomotor development that becomes apparent in the first months of life

Name: hypomyelinating leukodystrophy 8 with or without oligodontia and-or hypogonadotropic hypogonadism
Definition: A hypomyelinating leukodystrophy characterized by autosomal recessive inheritance of early childhood onset of cerebellar ataxia

Name: hypomyelinating leukodystrophy 6
Definition: A hypomyelinating leukodystrophy characterized by infant or early childhood onset of delayed motor development and gait instability
Synonym: hypomyelination with atrophy of basal ganglia and cerebellum

Name: hypomyelinating leukodystrophy 14
Definition: An early infantile epileptic encephalopathy that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the GABBR2 gene on chromosome 9q22.
